{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_52","type":"agent_message","text":"Patched [TckExtension.java](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge8/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/4950-e69952a2/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/TckExtension.java:184) so `diffCoordinates` no longer forces a `getTestDir(...)` lookup for every strict coordinate. It now exits early when no test files changed and skips unrelated coordinates whose test directory is missing, which prevents `generateChangedMetadataTestMatrix` from failing on stray metadata-only entries like the local `org.scodec:scodec-core_3:2.2.0` directory.\n\nAdded a regression test in [TckExtensionTests.java](/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge8/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/4950-e69952a2/tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/harness/TckExtensionTests.java:166) that builds a temp git repo with a changed library plus an unrelated metadata-only library with no test dir and verifies `diffCoordinates` still returns the changed coordinate.\n\nVerified with `./gradlew -p tests/tck-build-logic test --tests org.graalvm.internal.tck.harness.TckExtensionTests` and `GITHUB_OUTPUT=/tmp/tmp_i36ar4s ./gradlew generateChangedMetadataTestMatrix -PbaseCommit=FETCH_HEAD -PnewCommit=HEAD`; both succeeded."}}
